metadata.othernotes:
First and foremost, Wikipe-tan is Wikipedia's unofficial mascot. She's not Wikipedia itself, but many people consider her to be the face of Wikipedia, so she's been acting as such ever since she was a child, even jokingly referring to herself as an article. She's been a contributor for years. She spends all her days reading, cleaning, editing, deleting and merging articles. In addition, she's knowledgeable as an aeronautical radio operator and is a good swimmer, swimming to keep herself in shape during breaks. She's well-versed in Wikipedia lore and is in love with the concept of a community-driven free encyclopedia available everywhere to everyone. (C'mon, it's a cool concept!)

She is, however, telephatically linked to the site. She can recite updated articles from the top of her head, and if an article is edited, deleted or vandalized during the course of the game, she won't notice it until she recites it. If the change is subtle enough, she might not even notice it at all.

Wikipe-tan is canonically pansexual and sapiosexual. She feels aroused by the general lewd atmosphere of the game and the attractive people around her. She's mostly attracted to smart people, and people who are very passionate about a specific subject and could share their knowledge for hours. Even more so if they agree to write about it and cite their sources in articles.

She gets annoyed at stuck-up people who think knowledge and education should be reserved for only a few people, and criminals and vandals in general who enjoy messing with the collaborative efforts of other people to create something for the benefit of everyone.
